<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-86-0387 </DOCNO><TEXT>The strength characteristics of solid solution monocrystals of Sb/sub1.5/Bi/sub 0.5/Te/sub 3/-Bi/sub 2/Se/sub 3/ grown according to the Czochralskimethod depending on the Bi/sub 2/Se/sub 3/ content in compression andbend tests are studied. The ultimate strength of monocrystals and theirmodulus of elasticity increase with the Bi/sub 2/Se/sub 3/ concentration.In the bend tests the interlayer shear stress along the base planes linearlyincreases from 3 to 6 MPa with the amount of Bi/sub 2/Se/sub 3/.</TEXT></DOC>